  "curation": {
    "synopsis": "Standalone Ultramarines space-hulk novel. The hulk Fury drifts into Ultramar near Iax, its ancient hull carrying both Chaos taint and pre-Imperial archeo-tech that Mechanicus and Inquisition both want before the hulk is destroyed. Marneus Calgar commits five Ultramarines companies to a reconnaissance-in-force, with Inquisition strike-teams and Mechanicus skitarii embedded under their own command and their own agendas. The operation blurs the Imperium faction lines: chapter duty, Inquisition purification urge, and Mechanicus archeo-tech hunger pull in three directions while the hulk's xenos and Chaos defenders close in. A morally murky chapter-piece on inter-Imperium cooperation, with Calgar growing certain the hulk is itself a trap.",
